    <h3>One Line Summary</h3>
    <div class="compressed"><p>Discussion of Containers/Cgroups issues</p></div>
  

    <h3>Abstract</h3>
    <p>Specific issues that need discussing are</p>
<ul>
	<li>Checkpoint/Restart</li>
	<li>cgroup controller issues (mem and I/O)</li>
	<li>namespaces additions (including the network one)</li>
	<li>containerised <span class="caps">NFS</span></li>
</ul>

  

  

  

  <div class="record-controls">
    
    <a href="../events/LPC2011MC/proposals" class="cancelable">Back to list of proposals</a>
  </div>

  
    <h3>Speaker</h3>

    

<ul class='user_list'>

  

<li class="user_box vcard ">
  <a href="../users/9"><img alt="Photo_james_w800" class="user-photo photo" src="../system/photos/9/profile/photo_james_w800.jpg" /></a>
  <div class='user_head'>
    <h3><a href="../users/9" class="fn n" id="id_9" name="id_9">James E.J. Bottomley</a></h3>
      </div>
  <div class='user_body'>
    <div class='user_links'>
      <ul>
                
        
        
        
        
              </ul>
    </div>

  
    <h4>Biography</h4>
    <div class='note'>
      <p>James Bottomley is <span class="caps">CTO</span> of Server Virtualisation at Parallels and Linux Kernel maintainer of the <span class="caps">SCSI</span> subsystem, PA-<span class="caps">RISC</span> Linux and the 53c700 set of drivers. He has made contributions in the areas of x86 architecture and <span class="caps">SMP</span>, filesystems, storage and memory management and coherency.  He is currently a Director on the Board of the Linux Foundation and Chair of its Technical Advisory Board. He was born and<br />
grew up in the United Kingdom. He went to university  t Cambridge in 1985 for both his undergraduate and doctoral degrees. He joined AT&amp;T Bell labs in 1995 to work on Distributed Lock Manager technology for clustering. In 1997 he moved to the LifeKeeper High Availability project. In 2000 he helped found SteelEye Technology, Inc as Software Architect and later as Vice President and <span class="caps">CTO</span>.  He joined Novell in 2008 as a Distinguished Engineer at Novell&#8217;s <span class="caps">SUSE</span> Labs and  arallels in 2011.</p>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
      
  </div>
</li>
</ul>


  







